Tastefully fully renovated to blend classic beauty with contemporary family comfort. With neutral tones and quality finishes, this home offers a modern pad for couples, growing families and down-sizers. Designed and styled for easy living, the home represents excellent value and affordability for those wishing to enter the property market with certainty. The functional kitchen and sunny family / dining area are combined and overlooking the secure and private backyard, perfect for pet lovers.

Impressive throughout, the home is situated in a highly desirable quiet street with the convenience of local schools, shops and sports facilities just a short drive away. Its modern, fully updated kitchen features stainless steel appliances including a dishwasher and is well-appointed boasting ample cabinetry and generous counter space, while the pristine tiled bathroom comes equipped with shower and tub facilities. Surrounding the home are usable, and multiple level areas perfect for kids to play and easy to maintain.

- Short walk to parks, primary school and public transport;
- Lovely North and Easterly aspects, perfect for capturing the best of the sunlight;
- Charming low-set home with multiple large outdoor entertaining areas;
- Large windows allow for a lot of natural light;
- Impressive, recently renovated through-out;
- The master bedroom enjoys the luxury of full-length windows and built-in wardrobe;
- Cozy but airy 2 other bedrooms;
- Sleek and functional family bathroom with separate toilet;
- Large outdoor alfresco entertainment area overlooking the manicured gardens;
- Grassed area for the growing family;
- Single carport with storage and separate shed;
- Off-street parking for cars, trailers or boats.

Enjoy your years here in this lovely neighbourhood with all the amenities nearby. This fully renovated on one level home is made for low maintenance and comfortable living.

This brick home is “move in ready”, with all the modern features you desire.

This residence is appealing in every sense, so don’t delay – call Brett Russell now to arrange your viewing!

Presenting a rare opportunity in a sought after and convenient location, this single level residence sits on a flat parcel of land with lots of potential. The size, style and sophistication of the open plan living/dining areas are complemented by a stylish, well-equipped kitchen. Designed for the aspiring chef, the contemporary kitchen is adorned with stone bench-tops, gas stove, quality stainless steel appliances, free-standing SMEG Victorian cooker with 6 gas burners, 2 ovens / a grill, splash-back window and an array of cupboard storage. To round off this great family home is a versatile laundry and a double garage (doubled as a granny flat / teenagers retreat / lounge area) with drive through access to the rear yard. Perfect for a trailer or boat. The backyard is fully fenced, pet and child friendly.

The beautifully presented brick home is basked in sun and surrounded by expansive manicured gardens. The 3 bedrooms are cozy, and the natural light that flows through makes a comfortable and relaxing personal space. The main bedroom has a ensuite. The family bathroom features a bath, walk-in shower and separate toilet, all renovated and modern. Enjoying garden views in every direction, the home has been designed for complete privacy, surrounded by established, landscaped grounds and open lawn areas.

- Quiet cul-de-sac location, close to schools, shops, parks and transport;
- The solid timber floors are standout in quality and style;
- High ceilings, air conditioning, screens and blinds;
- Well maintained spacious kitchen with leafy green outlook;
- The master suite includes a spacious and contemporary ensuite and built in-robes;
- Brand new carpet in all bedrooms for warmth and comfort;
- Fabulous Pergola at the rear with easy to maintain flooring and garden views;
- Stay perfectly climatized all year round with ducted heating and cooling;
- This home has plenty of storage throughout and beautiful lighting in each and every room;
- Separate studio with toilet. Vinyl flooring throughout;
- Various storage options at the rear of the property;
- Custom glass panel garage door;
- Sunken lounge room;
- Separate stylish study nook;
- VJ panelling in living and dining areas, and study;
- Double glazed windows;
- Wall and ceiling insulation;
- Irrigation to lawn and all garden beds;
- Canberra Blend lawn featuring green all year round;
- Ducted gas heating;
- Aircon in bedrooms and living room;
- Solid spotted gum timber floors;
- Freshly painted throughout;
- Security alarm and custom security gate;
- USB ports throughout;
- French doors onto entertaining deck (36m2);
- Double-wide driveway.

Living on this peaceful street in the sought after suburb of Gowrie your family will enjoy an enviable position that puts you within walking distance to Schools, parks, caf&#233;’s and shops, not to mention public transport links in all directions. This property is set on a street that is right out of a fairytale – leafy, quiet, tranquil and simply beautiful. The double garage is oversized and has amazing storage.

Do not miss your chance to secure this desirable house!

This well cared for and loved apartment in the boutique “Elan” complex is ready for a fastidious owner.

In an unbeatable location and very close to public transport (700 metres from the tram), cafe&#39;s, bars, green spaces, local schools, shops and a town centre growing on a daily basis this two bedroom, two bathroom, two car parks townhouse, simply must be at the top of your list of properties to inspect.

This impressive beautifully styled townhouse presents an ideal opportunity to secure a low maintenance lifestyle of comfort and convenience. On a single level it boasts a great size living room at the front of the property, fantastic functional kitchen and separate dining area. The property is serviced by two large bedrooms, ensuite to the master bedroom, large main bathroom with a well concealed laundry and separate toilet. Both bedrooms have huge wardrobes and great natural light.

The complex offers a swimming pool (with a planned upgrade to be heated in 2023), spacious communal picnic areas for additional entertainment options and a community garden.

Features include:

- Spacious and light filled living area at front of property and separate dining area opening out to a large outdoor are;
- Sleek modern kitchen with large bench-tops, electric cooking, dishwasher, microwave space and under-bench oven;
- Two large bedrooms, both with built in robes, with main bedroom having ensuite and access through sliding door to outside area;
- Well appointed bathroom with a shower over bath, custom made vanity and concealed laundry;
- Separate Toilet near main bathroom;
- Quality floor coverings and blinds throughout;
- Contemporary fa&#231;ade and landscaped gardens;
- Split System air conditioning in living room and main bedroom;
- Fast internet connected to Canberra VDSL fibre optic network (with speeds of 100Mbps) with ethernet ports available in every room. 
- Double allocated carpark with large shed and plenty of extra parking off street;
- Swimming pool in the complex;
- Secure Backyard with roller shutters for both back windows;
- Established shared gardens with mature trees.
- Community garden with plots available to rent.
- A recently installed solar PV system powers communal facilities at the apartment complex (such as pool pumps), keeping strata fees low compared to similar apartment complexes.
- Next door to Old Canberra Inn, accessible by a concealed back-gate at the property, arguably the best pub in Canberra.
- Close to Tilley’s, The Front, O’Connor Ridge, Lyneham wetlands, light rail, Dickson shops and restaurants.
- Bus stop to city on doorstep.
- 15 min cycle to city or ANU along excellent bike paths.

